<subSubSection id="C31BC687FFB9F77DF298FD8CEA93D4F6" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="87" pageId="2" pageNumber="86" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BBE950CFFB9F77CF298FD8CECF5D2DE" blockId="2.[151,1436,572,706]" pageId="2" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis id="B975491EFFB9F77CF298FD8CEF21D266" bold="true" box="[199,345,608,634]" pageId="2" pageNumber="86">Description.</emphasis>
Sex unknown. Most of the body missing, the amber piece only carries an imprint of the anterior half of its upper part, the inclusion of antennae and the anterior leg in milky substance. Upperside light brown (quite probably red in the live specimen; 
<figureCitation id="133A8989FFB9F77CF043FD44EC19D2DE" box="[540,609,680,706]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1555,1579]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,728,1529]" captionTargetId="figure-137@2.[156,1432,728,1529]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. General view of Helcophorus (Thibeteros) ekaterinae, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6498052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6498052/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="86">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133A8989FFB9F77CF030FD44ECF8D2DE" box="[623,640,680,706]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1126,1150]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,181,1101]" captionTargetId="figure-24@3.[161,1426,181,1101]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pronotum and the base of elytra of Helcophorus (Thibeteros) ekaterinae, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6498067" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6498067/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="86">2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF7EC584FFB9F77CF2C8F9FFEDEFD637" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6498052" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6498052" box="[151,919,1555,1579]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6498052/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="86" startId="2.[151,250,1555,1579]" targetBox="[156,1432,728,1529]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="8BBE950CFFB9F77CF2C8F9FFEDEFD637" blockId="2.[151,919,1555,1579]" box="[151,919,1555,1579]" pageId="2" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis id="B975491EFFB9F77CF2C8F9FFEF75D637" bold="true" box="[151,269,1555,1579]" pageId="2" pageNumber="86">FIGURE 1</emphasis>
. General view of 
<taxonomicName id="4C01EE8FFFB9F77CF39CF9FFED42D637" box="[451,826,1555,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Helcophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ekaterinae" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Thibeteros">
<emphasis id="B975491EFFB9F77CF39CF9FFEC3ED637" box="[451,582,1555,1579]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="86">Helcophorus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B975491EFFB9F77CF00AF9FFECB8D637" box="[597,704,1555,1579]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="86">Thibeteros</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B975491EFFB9F77CF090F9FFED42D637" box="[719,826,1555,1579]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="86">ekaterinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A246F465FFB9F77CF119F9FFEDEFD637" box="[838,919,1555,1579]" pageId="2" pageNumber="86" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BBE950CFFB9F77CF298F9B5ED4BD68B" blockId="2.[151,1437,1625,2012]" pageId="2" pageNumber="86">
Head about as wide as pronotum. Eyes bulging, relatively large, their diameter ca. 1/2 length of pronotum (
<figureCitation id="133A8989FFB9F77CF734F9B5EEDDD68B" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1555,1579]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,728,1529]" captionTargetId="figure-137@2.[156,1432,728,1529]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. General view of Helcophorus (Thibeteros) ekaterinae, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6498052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6498052/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="86">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133A8989FFB9F77CF2ECF991EEBCD68B" box="[179,196,1661,1687]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1126,1150]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,181,1101]" captionTargetId="figure-24@3.[161,1426,181,1101]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pronotum and the base of elytra of Helcophorus (Thibeteros) ekaterinae, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6498067" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6498067/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="86">2</figureCitation>
). Antennomeres 2 and 3 of approximately equal length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBE950CFFB9F77CF298F94EED49D73B" blockId="2.[151,1437,1625,2012]" pageId="2" pageNumber="86">
Pronotum transverse, ca. 1.5 times wider than long, semi-trapezoidal, with pronounced acute posterior angles; median areole rhomboidal, broad in the middle, connected with lateral sides with narrow oblique, slightly curved costae. Scutellum (postnotal plate of mesonotal scutellum) transverse, parallel-sided, medially moderately triangularly notched, with broadly rounded distal lobes (
<figureCitation id="133A8989FFB9F77CF0E1F8E1ED7DD73B" box="[702,773,1805,1831]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1555,1579]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,728,1529]" captionTargetId="figure-137@2.[156,1432,728,1529]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. General view of Helcophorus (Thibeteros) ekaterinae, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6498052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6498052/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="86">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133A8989FFB9F77CF14CF8E1ED5CD73B" box="[787,804,1805,1831]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1126,1150]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,181,1101]" captionTargetId="figure-24@3.[161,1426,181,1101]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pronotum and the base of elytra of Helcophorus (Thibeteros) ekaterinae, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6498067" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6498067/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="86">2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBE950CFFB9F77CF298F8DDECE7D78F" blockId="2.[151,1437,1625,2012]" pageId="2" pageNumber="86">
Elytra elongate, flattened, noticeably widened distally; with four primary costae, of which third distinctly stouter; interstices with rectangular transverse, their width ca. 2 times exceeding their length, cells; pubescence sparse and short, almost indistinguishable (
<figureCitation id="133A8989FFB9F77CF073F895EC0BD78F" box="[556,627,1913,1939]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1555,1579]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,728,1529]" captionTargetId="figure-137@2.[156,1432,728,1529]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. General view of Helcophorus (Thibeteros) ekaterinae, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6498052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6498052/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="86">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133A8989FFB9F77CF0DEF895ECEAD78F" box="[641,658,1913,1939]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1126,1150]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,181,1101]" captionTargetId="figure-24@3.[161,1426,181,1101]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pronotum and the base of elytra of Helcophorus (Thibeteros) ekaterinae, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6498067" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6498067/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="86">2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBE950CFFB9F77CF298F871EF63D7C0" blockId="2.[151,1437,1625,2012]" pageId="2" pageNumber="86">
Length (of the roughly anterior half of the individual): 
<quantity id="4CF938E9FFB9F77CF166F871EDECD7A4" box="[825,916,1949,1976]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="86" unit="mm" value="6.5">6.5 mm</quantity>
. Width at humeri: 2.0 mm. Length of antenna ca. 
<quantity id="4CF938E9FFB9F77CF2E1F82DEF6FD7C0" box="[190,279,1985,2012]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.4" pageId="2" pageNumber="86" unit="mm" value="4.4">4.4 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF7EC584FFB8F77DF2C8FB8AEA2AD462" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6498067" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6498067" box="[151,1106,1126,1150]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6498067/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="87" startId="3.[151,250,1126,1150]" targetBox="[161,1426,181,1101]" targetPageId="3">
