<paragraph id="8BBE950CFFB8F77DF298FB40EA93D4F6" blockId="3.[151,1436,1196,1547]" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">
<emphasis id="B975491EFFB8F77DF298FB40EF0AD4DA" bold="true" box="[199,370,1196,1222]" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">Syninclusions.</emphasis>
SIZK UA-28623: 2 Dolichopodaidae, 2 
<taxonomicName id="4C01EE8FFFB8F77DF117FB40EDB0D4DA" box="[840,968,1196,1222]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Formicidae</taxonomicName>
(1 
<taxonomicName id="4C01EE8FFFB8F77DF1AEFB41EAB3D4DB" box="[1009,1227,1197,1223]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Yantaromyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B975491EFFB8F77DF1AEFB41EAD8D4DA" box="[1009,1184,1197,1222]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">Yantaromyrmex</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
), Aranei, cobweb; SIZK UA-28624: 2 
<taxonomicName id="4C01EE8FFFB8F77DF327FB3CEF83D4F6" box="[376,507,1232,1258]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Formicidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C01EE8FFFB8F77DF05AFB3CECD0D4F6" box="[517,680,1232,1258]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chironomidae</taxonomicName>
, Cecydomyiidae, Collembola, Entomobryomorpha.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31BC687FFB8F77DF298FB18EAAAD52E" pageId="3" pageNumber="87" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BBE950CFFB8F77DF298FB18EAAAD52E" blockId="3.[151,1436,1196,1547]" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">
<emphasis id="B975491EFFB8F77DF298FB18EF36D512" bold="true" box="[199,334,1268,1294]" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">Etymology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C01EE8FFFB8F77DF30BFB18EC88D512" box="[340,752,1268,1295]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Helcophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ekaterinae" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Thibeteros">
<emphasis id="B975491EFFB8F77DF30BFB18EF9DD512" box="[340,485,1268,1294]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">Helcophorus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B975491EFFB8F77DF3ABFB18EC13D512" box="[500,619,1268,1294]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">Thibeteros</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B975491EFFB8F77DF025FB18EC88D512" box="[634,752,1268,1294]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">ekaterinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B975491EFFB8F77DF0A9FB18ED37D512" bold="true" box="[758,847,1268,1294]" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A246F465FFB8F77DF0A9FB18ED37D512" box="[758,847,1268,1294]" pageId="3" pageNumber="87" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is named after our colleague Dr 
<taxonomicName id="4C01EE8FFFB8F77DF6E7FB18EBE4D512" authority="Sidorchuk" authorityName="Sidorchuk" box="[1208,1436,1268,1294]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Ekaterina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ekaterina Sidorchuk</taxonomicName>
(Moscow), a prominent paleoentomologist who lost her life in a diving accident in the 
<collectingCountry id="F316D59CFFB8F77DF63CFAF4EAB7D52E" box="[1123,1231,1304,1330]" name="Maldives" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">Maldives</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31BC687FFB8F77DF298FAD0EAF7D616" pageId="3" pageNumber="87" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BBE950CFFB8F77DF298FAD0EAF7D616" blockId="3.[151,1436,1196,1547]" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">
<emphasis id="B975491EFFB8F77DF298FAD0EF3AD54A" bold="true" box="[199,322,1340,1366]" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species may be distinguished from the extant members of the same subgenus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C01EE8FFFB8F77DF71FFAD1EFD4D566" authority="Kazantsev, 2000" authorityName="Kazantsev" authorityYear="2000" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Helcophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricolor" subGenus="Thibeteros">
<emphasis id="B975491EFFB8F77DF71FFAD1EB24D54A" box="[1344,1372,1341,1366]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">H.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B975491EFFB8F77DF731FAD0EBEBD54A" box="[1390,1427,1340,1366]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">Th.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B975491EFFB8F77DF2C8FA8CEE95D566" box="[151,237,1376,1402]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">tricolor</emphasis>
Kazantsev, 2000
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C01EE8FFFB8F77DF3BEFA8DEDEAD567" authority="Kazantsev, 2015" authorityName="Kazantsev" authorityYear="2015" box="[481,914,1376,1403]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Helcophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sichuanensis" subGenus="Thibeteros">
<emphasis id="B975491EFFB8F77DF3BEFA8DEF85D566" box="[481,509,1377,1402]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">H.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B975491EFFB8F77DF053FA8CEC49D566" box="[524,561,1376,1402]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">Th.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B975491EFFB8F77DF01EFA8CECA8D566" box="[577,720,1376,1402]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">sichuanensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF90E8FDFFB8F77DF089FA8DEDEAD567" author="Kazantsev, S. V." box="[726,914,1376,1403]" pageId="3" pageNumber="87" pagination="383 - 389" refId="ref2761" refString="Kazantsev, S. V. (2015) New taxa of Helcophorus Fairmaire, 1891, with a key to species of the genus (Coleoptera: Lycidae). In: Hartmann, M. &amp; Weipert, J. (Eds.), Biodiversitat und Naturausstattung im Himalaya. Band 5. Verein der Freunde &amp; Forderer des Naturkundemuseums Erfurt e. V., Erfurt, pp. 383 - 389." type="book chapter" year="2015">Kazantsev, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by the noticeably more transverse elytral cells between the primary costae and narrowly notched scutellum with broadly rounded distal lobes (
<figureCitation id="133A8989FFB8F77DF6E8FA68EA85D582" box="[1207,1277,1412,1438]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1555,1579]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,728,1529]" captionTargetId="figure-137@2.[156,1432,728,1529]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. General view of Helcophorus (Thibeteros) ekaterinae, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6498052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6498052/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133A8989FFB8F77DF755FA68EB62D582" box="[1290,1306,1412,1438]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1126,1150]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,181,1101]" captionTargetId="figure-24@3.[161,1426,181,1101]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pronotum and the base of elytra of Helcophorus (Thibeteros) ekaterinae, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6498067" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6498067/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">2</figureCitation>
), compared to less transverse elytral cells and broadly notched scutellum with narrowed distal lobes in the extant species of the subgenus (
<figureCitation id="133A8989FFB8F77DF34FFA20EF2FD5FA" box="[272,343,1484,1510]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–4" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1792,1816]" captionTargetBox="[219,1367,540,1759]" captionTargetId="figure-179@4.[204,1384,525,1769]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 3–4. General view of extant Helcophorus: 3 – H. (s. str.) miniatus; 4 – H. (Thibeteros) tricolor (after Kazantsev, 2015)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6498076" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6498076/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). It differs from the only other fossil 
<taxonomicName id="4C01EE8FFFB8F77DF15BFA20ED89D5FA" box="[772,1009,1484,1510]" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">
<emphasis id="B975491EFFB8F77DF15BFA20EDEDD5FA" box="[772,917,1484,1510]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">Helcophorus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C01EE8FFFB8F77DF1A1FA21EAADD5FA" authorityName="Winkler" authorityYear="1987" box="[1022,1237,1484,1511]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Hiekeolycus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" isSensuStricto="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="berendti">
<emphasis id="B975491EFFB8F77DF1A1FA21EA61D5FA" box="[1022,1049,1485,1510]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">H.</emphasis>
(s. str.) 
<emphasis id="B975491EFFB8F77DF626FA20EAADD5FA" box="[1145,1237,1484,1510]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">berendti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by the distinctly sparser elytral vestiture, relatively larger eyes, and more transverse elytral cells (
<figureCitation id="133A8989FFB8F77DF643FA1CEA1BD616" box="[1052,1123,1520,1546]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1555,1579]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,728,1529]" captionTargetId="figure-137@2.[156,1432,728,1529]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. General view of Helcophorus (Thibeteros) ekaterinae, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6498052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6498052/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133A8989FFB8F77DF62EFA1CEAFAD616" box="[1137,1154,1520,1546]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1126,1150]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,181,1101]" captionTargetId="figure-24@3.[161,1426,181,1101]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pronotum and the base of elytra of Helcophorus (Thibeteros) ekaterinae, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6498067" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6498067/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="87">2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
